    <text>
        <body>
            
            
            <div xml:id="Vespers"> 
                <interpGrp type="poembox">
                    <interp ana="#form" type="vespers"></interp>
                    <interp ana="#tone" type="boy"></interp>
                    <interp ana="#topic" type="little"></interp>
                </interpGrp>
                <lg> 
               
                    <l>Little Boy kneels at the foot of the bed,</l>
                    <l>  Droops on the little hands little gold head.</l>
                    <l> Hush! Hush! Whisper who dares!
                        <l> Christopher Robin is saying his prayers.</l>
               
                        <l>God bless Mummy. I know that's right.</l>
                        <l> Wasn't it fun in the bath to-night?</l>
                        <l> The cold's so cold, and the hot's so hot.</l>
                        <l> Oh! God bless Daddy - I quite forgot.</l>
               
                        <l> If I open my fingers a little bit more,</l>
                        <l> I can see Nanny's dressing-gown on the door.</l>
                        <l> It's a beautiful blue, but it hasn't a hood.</l>
                        <l> Oh! God bless Nanny and make her good.</l>
               
                        <l> Mine has a hood, and I lie in bed,</l>
                        <l> And pull the hood right over my head,</l>
                        <l> And I shut my eyes, and I curl up small,</l>
                        <l>And nobody knows that I'm there at all.</l>
               
                        <l>Oh! Thank you, God, for a lovely day.</l>
                        <l>And what was the other I had to say?</l>
                        <l>I said "Bless Daddy," so what can it be?</l>
                        <l>Oh! Now I remember it. God bless Me.</l>
               
                        <l>Little Boy kneels at the foot of the bed,</l>
                        <l> Droops on the little hands little gold head.</l>
                        <l> Hush! Hush! Whisper who dares!</l>
                        <l> Christopher Robin is saying his prayers.</l>
               
                        <l> Source: https://www.familyfriendpoems.com/poem/vespers-by-a-a-milne</l>
                    
